The Metadata Management team of the NOS Assistant of the Chief Information Officer (NOS ACIO IT) is responsible for the publication of geospatial metadata published by NOS Program Offices to its NOS Data Explorer Geoportal and the federal clearinghouse, Data.gov geoportal.  The NOS Metadata Management team reviews for metadata standards and conventions set down by guidance.  NOS Program Office metadata managers author the content of the geospatial metadata.  For questions about metadata publication, direct inquiries to the NOS ACIO IT Metadata Management team. Coast Survey's Wrecks and Obstructions database contains information on the identified submerged wrecks and obstructions within the U.S. maritime boundaries. The data includes the position of each feature (latitude and longitude) along with a brief description. Information to populate the database comes from what is currently available on the electronic navigational chart (ENC) and Coast Survey's Automated Wrecks and Obstructions Information System (AWOIS) database. </gco:CharacterString>    </gmd:abstract>    <gmd:purpose>     <gco:CharacterString>The Office of Coast Survey is responsible for charting the Nation's waterways to ensure safe marine transportation and navigation.  Hydrographic surveying is a critical component of this process.  The AWOIS and charted (Electronic Navigational Charts - ENCs) wrecks and obstructions have been identified over the course of OCS' history and cataloged in a database for use in survey planning and also for inclusion on the nautical chart suite.  The database and associated mapping services are provided to the public as a related service for general usage. </gco:CharacterString>    </gmd:purpose>    <gmd:credit/>    <gmd:status>
